  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Child protection project in Mozambique</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Child protection is an increasingly alarming issue in the target communities, where growing multinational investment is driving an environment that puts children at greater risk for abuse and neglect.  This PPA funded project will provide the necessary resources to improve technical capacity and increase interventions in child protection.  The project will  work to strengthen the capacity of existing networks and local partners, and will support children and young people to contribute their perspective on protection issues, and to share their experiences and expectations of the mechanisms and systems that are there to protect them.</narrative>
  </description>
